  "texts": [
    "As previously highlighted, the authors' focus was exclusively on node and link privacy issues.",
    "For the category of node privacy, they examined studies that implemented anonymization through Naïve Anonymization and Node Perturbation methods.",
    "After analyzing the surveyed research, they concluded that there are predominantly two strategies to perturb nodes in social networks, specifically Random Perturbation and Constrained Perturbation.",
    "Additionally, in terms of link privacy, they examined research introducing social network anonymization techniques based on Edge Perturbation and Random Walk methodologies, from which they determined that there are generally five distinct approaches to perturb the edges in a social network.",
    "These methods include Intact Edges, Partial-Edge Removal, Cluster-Edge Anonymization, Cluster-Edge Anonymization with Constraints, and Removed Edges.It is worth mentioning that Siddula et al."
